My brother and his friends were visiting from SoCal the other day, and original plan was to go hit up an AYCE Sushi place for dinner, before one of his friends got sick before dinner.
So I ended up taking the group here and ordering Chinese take-out to bring back and eat in the room.
Everything was great, even the soup noodle that we ordered(which was packed in a way that makes it still good to assemble in the room: very hot soup in one large container, the rest of the components in others, including the thinly sliced rare beef which we "shabu shabu" in the hot broth back in the hotel room).
As a crew that is used to really good Chinese food at competitive prices from Monterey Park, they all agreed that it was very good for Las Vegas.
I dropped by again today to grab some lunch specials and work my way through their lunch special menus.
The Curry Chicken was excellent, and the way the chef cooks the chicken was done in a way that truly shows that he has some serious culinary background.
The chicken was still soft and succulent, plus the portion was generous.
Good flavor, fine techniques, generous portions, and attractive prices =  I will be a frequent repeat customer as long as I live in Las Vegas.
As for the AYCE Hotpot/fondue, the counter where all the ingredients are usually kept is empty today.
The waitress told me that the temperature has been warm, so they stop putting out the ingredients out and offering it as AYCE.
Hot pot is still offered but must be ordered a la carte, so depending on how much you can eat your final tab may be less or more expensive than before, but allthe ingredients will be that much fresher.
Here is a brief price list: All veggies are $2.95 - tofu, spinach, cabbage,mushrooms, wontons, egg noodles, etc.
Some meats are $3.95 - pork blood, sliced chicken, sliced beef, pork intestine, pork liver, pork kidney.
Some meats are $4.95 - Sliced Fatty Beef, Sliced Fatty Lamb and Beef Tripe.
All Seafoods are $4.95 - Clams, Shrimps, Sliced Fish, Squids, Fish Balls, Fish Tofu and Mussels.
Lobsters $12.95  (I think it is a fair deal) Crab $12.95 Oysters $5.95 Scallops $5.95

